OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1782161281
OL,3,CSir Keir Starmer steps down as Labour
OL,4,Cleader
OL,6,F"I want to thank all of those friends
OL,7,Fand colleagues who have been at my
OL,8,Fside for these past six years or so
OL,9,Ffor their incredible commitment,
OL,10,Fservice and support," he added.
OL,12,F"I want to thank the brilliant Number
OL,13,F10 staff and our country's
OL,14,Fextraordinary civil service, who
OL,15,Fdedicate their lives to public service.
OL,17,F"And when I leave, the biggest job in
OL,18,Fthe country. I shall spend more time
OL,19,Fon the most important job.
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@AOUyD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30509
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1782161281
OL,3,CSir Keir Starmer steps down as Labour
OL,4,Cleader
OL,6,F"Being the best husband I can to my
OL,7,Ffantastic wife, Vic, who has been a
OL,8,Frock by my side, through good times
OL,9,Fand bad. And being the best dad I can
OL,10,Fto my beautiful children, who are my
OL,11,Fpride and my joy."
OL,13,FCabinet ministers have paid tribute to
OL,14,FStarmer following his announcement,
OL,15,Fincluding Work and Pensions Secretary
OL,16,FPat McFadden, who wrote on social
OL,17,Fmedia: "The Labour Party and the
OL,18,Fcountry owes a great deal to Keir
OL,19,FStarmer.
OL,26,@nD@AOUyD@HOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30510
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1782161281
OL,3,CSir Keir Starmer steps down as Labour
OL,4,Cleader
OL,6,F"Brought Labour back from its worst
OL,7,Fresult in living memory. Won a
OL,8,Fmajority at a general election which
OL,9,Fhistory shows does not happen often
OL,10,Ffor Labour leaders. And led the
OL,11,Fcountry through difficult times."
OL,13,FIn a post on X, Housing Secretary
OL,14,FSteve Reed said: "Keir Starmer brought
OL,15,FLabour back from the brink, won a
OL,16,Flandslide majority against all the
OL,17,Fodds, and is changing Britain for the
OL,18,Fbetter.
OL,20,F"Thank you Keir, we are proud of you."
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@aO]vD@ROU|D@AOU|D@fO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/14
