OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1782161281
OL,3,CSir Keir Starmer steps down as Labour
OL,4,Cleader
OL,6,F"Thank you, dear Keir."
OL,8,FCriticism came from Conservative
OL,9,FLeader Kemi Badenoch, who called
OL,10,F"Starmer a terrible Prime Minister"
OL,11,Fbefore adding that "We need to get
OL,12,FBritain working again".
OL,14,FReform UK leader Nigel Farage called
OL,15,Ffor a general election in the wake of
OL,16,Fthe resignation, writing on X: "If
OL,17,FLabour thinks it can shove another
OL,18,Fprofessional politician into No 10, it
OL,19,Fhas another thing coming."
OL,26,@xD@`OU{D@ZO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/14
