OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1782161281
OL,3,CSir Keir Starmer steps down as Labour
OL,4,Cleader
OL,6,FOther opposition figures stopped short
OL,7,Fof demanding an election, but urged
OL,8,FStarmer's successor to be bold.
OL,10,FLiberal Democrat leader Sir Ed Davey
OL,11,Fsaid: "Whoever becomes prime minister
OL,12,Fneeds to drop the caution and
OL,13,Fcomplacency and show the ambition our
OL,14,Fcountry deserves."
OL,26,@sD@GOUvD@RO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/14
